## Fix 1 — Shared `handleValidationErrors` ✅
The function previously existed in two files with identical code. It now lives in one file and is imported by both validators:
```js
// Before: two identical copies
// After: single import
const handleValidationErrors = require('./handleValidationErrors');
```
Change the error shape once → updates everywhere instantly.

---

## Fix 2 — Query Param Validation ✅

`GET /api/properties?minPrice=abc&minBedrooms=-5` now returns:
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "errors": [
    { "field": "minPrice",    "message": "minPrice must be a non-negative number" },
    { "field": "minBedrooms", "message": "minBedrooms must be a non-negative integer" }
  ]
}
```
Instead of silently producing wrong results. All 12 query params are validated:

| Param | Rule |
|---|---|
| `page` | Integer ≥ 1 |
| `limit` | Integer 1–50 |
| `sort` | One of: newest, oldest, price_asc, price_desc |
| `propertyType` | Valid enum |
| `listingType` | Valid enum |
| `status` | Valid enum |
| `minPrice` / `maxPrice` | Float ≥ 0 |
| `minBedrooms` / `maxBedrooms` | Integer ≥ 0 |
| `keyword` / `city` / `region` | String, max 100 chars |

Numeric params also use `.toInt()` / `.toFloat()` — so `buildFilter` always receives correct types, never NaN.

