## Fix 5 — Phone Format Validation ✅

`phone` on registration now validates international phone formats:
```js
body('phone')
  .optional({ checkFalsy: true })   // empty string is treated as "not provided"
  .isMobilePhone('any', { strictMode: false })
  .withMessage('Please provide a valid phone number')
```
`strictMode: false` accepts numbers without country code prefix — so `0712345678` is valid alongside `+254712345678`.

